HEADWORD: Ericius
<hw>E*ri"ci*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
hedgehog.]</ety> <def>The Vulgate rendering of the Hebrew word
<xex>qip⟦omac⟧d</xex>, which in the ⟦ldquo⟧Authorized Version⟦rdquo⟧ is
translated <sig>bittern</sig>, and in the Revised Version,
<sig>porcupine</sig>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will make it [Babylon] a possession for the <qex>ericius</qex>
and pools of waters.</q> <rj><qau>Is. xiv. 23 (Douay
version).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ericolin</ent>⟦br⟧
